The White House Task Force on Middle Class Families held a meeting in Ohio to discuss American manufacturing in the 21st century. Vice President Biden, Ohio Governor Ted Strickland, Secretary of Commerce Gary Locke, and Director of Recovery for Auto Communities and Workers Ed Montgomery were in attendance. During the meeting, new initiatives were discussed to prepare the manufacturing economy for the future. Vice President Biden also announced the creation of the White House Council on Automotive Communities and Workers through an Executive Order. The Department of Commerce announced the expansion of the National Innovation Marketplace, which aims to revitalize supply chains and help manufacturers transition to emerging technologies and new market opportunities. The meeting included various manufacturing experts, and the investments discussed are intended to support manufacturing workers and communities.